+## Review Reply Draft
+
+### T-214-01
+
+Fixed the reopened fallback payload regression. `build_policy_preview(...)` now normalizes `manual_review` to `human_review_required` before building the payload, and the fallback response now keeps both `approval_state` and `requires_human_review` when `preview_enabled` is `False`.
+
+### T-214-02
+
+Marked as duplicate of `T-214-01`. This thread describes the same reopened fallback payload issue, so it is covered by the same code change.
+
+### T-214-03
+
+Did not apply this suggestion. The export marks this thread outdated, and reviving legacy preview behavior on the current branch would move away from the normalized `human_review_required` path. No legacy preview branch or hint was reintroduced.
+
+### T-214-04
+
+Added a regression test in `tests/test_preview.py` that exercises `build_policy_preview(..., preview_enabled=False, approval_state="manual_review", ...)` and verifies the fallback payload keeps `approval_state="human_review_required"` and `requires_human_review=True`.
+
+### T-214-05
+
+Updated the approval policy docs so the fallback example matches the fixed payload and explicitly includes `approval_state` plus `requires_human_review`.
