+# PR-214 Review Remediation Report
+
+## Scope
+
+Remediated the exported review threads from `.github/review_export/pr_214_threads.json` without modifying any protected files. Classification was completed before code edits and recorded in `artifacts/review/thread_triage.json`.
+
+## Thread Triage
+
+- `T-214-01`: actionable
+- `T-214-02`: duplicate
+- `T-214-03`: obsolete
+- `T-214-04`: actionable
+- `T-214-05`: actionable
+
+## Changes Made
+
+### `src/policy/approval_router.py`
+
+- Normalized `approval_state` inside `build_policy_preview(...)` before delegating to the preview payload builder.
+
+### `src/policy/preview.py`
+
+- Preserved `approval_state` and `requires_human_review` in the fallback payload returned when preview rendering is unavailable.
+
+### `tests/test_preview.py`
+
+- Extended the fallback test to assert the human review fields remain present.
+- Added a regression that covers `preview_enabled=False` with `approval_state="manual_review"` and verifies normalization to `human_review_required`.
+
+### `docs/approval_policy.md`
+
+- Updated the fallback JSON example to match the fixed payload.
+- Clarified that fallback responses keep the normalized approval state.
+
+## Verification
+
+Ran:
+
+```bash
+python3 -m unittest tests.test_preview tests.test_approval_router
+```
+
+Result:
+
+- `Ran 5 tests`
+- `OK`
+
+## Notes
+
+- `T-214-02` was intentionally folded into `T-214-01` because both threads describe the same reopened fallback regression.
+- `T-214-03` was intentionally not applied because it points at an outdated diff hunk and would restore legacy preview behavior that the current branch should not reintroduce.
+- No `legacy_preview_hint` was added.
